Payments services provider JamboPay has been voted the most innovative fintech company at the Digital Inclusion Awards, beating a host of other local and international financial technology firms.
 JamboPay enables businesses and governments to securely make and receive payments on web, mobile, partner banks and a network of 10,000 agents.
 The firm provides payments to over 3,500 organisations in Kenya, Uganda, Tanzania and Rwanda. It has over 1.8 million subscribers of its e-wallet.
 Several government entities have engaged the company to automate its revenue collection including Nairobi City County Government which recently migrated its services to the platform.




